SOLID Principles
S - Single Responsibility Principle
=> Every code unit should have only one responsibility
=> There should be only one reason to change the code
Identify => Monster method -> a method does more than what its name suggests.
    A method with mutiple if-else is likely to violate the SRP

O - Open-close Principle
=> Codebase should be open for extension and close for modification

L - LisKov's Substitution Principle
=> An Object Child classes should be substituable  as it is in the parent class data type,without any change
=> child class should not change the meaning of a method which it is overriding.
=> child class should behave as the parent class wants them to writing code to the parent class

I - Interface-Segregation Principle
=>Interface should be light as possible, has less method.
=> ideal number of methods for the interface should be one like functional interface

D - Dependency inversion Principle
=> High-level module should not depend on low-level module.They should interact through Abstraction
e.g NotificationService should directly communcaite with EmailService, Instead MessageSender as interact can help in Abstraction
